      <title>Amaranth Hello World</title>
      <link>/posts/2025/09/amaranth-hello-world/</link>
      <pubDate>Fri, 12 Sep 2025 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>/posts/2025/09/amaranth-hello-world/</guid>
      <description>&lt;p&gt;I came across the &lt;code&gt;Amaranth&lt;/code&gt; project, which is yet another meta HDL language in Python. What I find interesting is that Amaranth implements some of the ideas I&amp;rsquo;ve had for years. The language has Verilog-like constructs that map to Verilog &lt;code&gt;If&lt;/code&gt; statements.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;h1 id=&#34;setup&#34;&gt;&#xA;  Setup&#xA;  &lt;a class=&#34;heading-link&#34; href=&#34;#setup&#34;&gt;&#xA;    &lt;i class=&#34;fa-solid fa-link&#34; aria-hidden=&#34;true&#34; title=&#34;Link to heading&#34;&gt;&lt;/i&gt;&#xA;    &lt;span class=&#34;sr-only&#34;&gt;Link to heading&lt;/span&gt;&#xA;  &lt;/a&gt;&#xA;&lt;/h1&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;The setup is easy. Just install it with pip, and you&amp;rsquo;re good to go.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34;&gt;&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; style=&#34;color:#e6edf3;background-color:#0d1117;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-bash&#34; data-lang=&#34;bash&#34;&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;pip install --upgrade &lt;span style=&#34;color:#a5d6ff&#34;&gt;&amp;#34;amaranth[builtin-yosys]&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h1 id=&#34;counter-example&#34;&gt;&#xA;  Counter Example&#xA;  &lt;a class=&#34;heading-link&#34; href=&#34;#counter-example&#34;&gt;&#xA;    &lt;i class=&#34;fa-solid fa-link&#34; aria-hidden=&#34;true&#34; title=&#34;Link to heading&#34;&gt;&lt;/i&gt;&#xA;    &lt;span class=&#34;sr-only&#34;&gt;Link to heading&lt;/span&gt;&#xA;  &lt;/a&gt;&#xA;&lt;/h1&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;The first example from the Amaranth website implements a counter with &lt;code&gt;limit&lt;/code&gt; as an internal signal and &lt;code&gt;ovf&lt;/code&gt; to indicate overflow.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
